This paper deals with opinion dynamics in a society of agents, which is a topic that falls under the sub-categories of social and information sciences. Specifically, the paper discusses a model for one-dimensional opinion dynamics, which suggests that it could fall under the categories of cs.SI (social and information networks), cs.SOC (computational social science), cs.DS (data structures and algorithms), cs.MA (multi-agent systems), and cs.GT (computational game theory). However, given the emphasis on social dynamics and the use of real values to measure opinions, cs.SI and cs.SOC are the most likely categories.
